Publicly traded REITS are staggered, like all real-estate companies, by the coronavirus.
We combed filings from mid-March to recent days and cherry-picked some interesting facts and prognostications.
Vornado Realty Trust’s Steven Roth, in his chairman’s letter accompanying the just-out 2019 annual report, called the “eye of the COVID-19 storm… a black swan apocalypse.
“The disruption to normal day to day life and normal work life is extraordinary but will hopefully be short-lived.
But Roth wrote, “We have wondered whether the work-from-home response to COVID-19 may become popular and affect office demand.